{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/265/comments/103759.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:39f19886f0aa..dc43ebdfb312?path=cmake%2FGazeboUtils.cmake"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/265/_/diff#comment-103759"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 265, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/265.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/265"}}, "title": "Added in ability to make QT tests."}, "content": {"raw": "Now that we have the DRI check on place, what do you think about starting to not generate/not running GUI based tests if not valid DRI capable display is found? Something like:\n\n\n```\n#!cmake\n\nIF (NOT VALID_DRI_DISPLAY)\n  macro (gz_build_qt_test)\n  endmacro()\nELSE()\n  ... current macro definition ...\nENDIF()\n```", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Now that we have the DRI check on place, what do you think about starting to not generate/not running GUI based tests if not valid DRI capable display is found? Something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-cmake\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nb\">IF</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">NOT</span> <span class=\"s\">VALID_DRI_DISPLAY</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"nb\">macro</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">gz_build_qt_test</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"nb\">endmacro</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">ELSE</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n  <span class=\"err\">...</span> <span class=\"err\">current</span> <span class=\"err\">macro</span> <span class=\"err\">definition</span> <span class=\"err\">...</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">ENDIF</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-02-01T09:56:22.953931+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42e